Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 4 14:37:02 2026 +0200

    fix(mcp-server): guard relation-backfill from invalidating valid edges; honest counts (026/026)
    
    Deep-review SEC-001 remediation: a relation-agnostic conflict guard (hasConflictingValidEdge, reusing relationsConflict) suppresses a committed backfill auto-edge that would invalidate an existing valid edge (manual or auto) on the same pair — closing the reciprocal lineage caused/contradicts self-invalidation. written/byRelation now derive from a committed valid-auto-edge delta (written=0 on re-run, excludes invalidated). Inner backfill schema is strict (typo'd opt-in keys throw). 5 maintainability P2s cleared. New relation-backfill-conflict.vitest.ts (reciprocal caused-survives + manual-edge-survives + re-run + byRelation + strict-schema); 179 tests green.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

