    - DR-014 (retention TOCTOU, data-loss): re-validate delete_after inside the
      delete transaction so a row un-expired by a concurrent writer between
      selection and deletion is not swept. New isStillExpired predicate + test.
    - DR-013 (adapter cache ignored dimensions): re-create the adapter on a
      cache-hit dimension mismatch, keeping the provider:model key so
      teardownEmbedderAfterSwap is unaffected. Regression test.
    - DR-001/015 (bootstrap ignored explicit provider): prefer an explicit
      EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER ahead of the local-first cascade (then fall back),
      mirroring resolveProvider() precedence. Regression test.
    
    Dispositioned, no code change:
    - DR-002-P1-002: the cited acquireLock does not exist; the real
      acquireFilesystemLock intentionally degrades to the in-process queue on
      timeout (belt-and-suspenders) — failing closed would break legitimate
      single-process use.
    - DR-017: already fixed at HEAD (embedder_status timestamp path is live).
    
    Verified: both @spec-kit workspaces build (tsc exit 0); retention 10/10,
    execution-router 14/14, auto-selection 9/9. dist/ is gitignored, rebuilt by
    the launcher at startup.
    
    Packet: 031-embedding-stack-hardening/008-deep-review-correctness-edges
    (Level 1, validate.sh --strict exit 0).
    
