commit 8a30db882014cff8b5941653eb88c9a1c2449740
Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 29 15:49:58 2026 +0200

    fix(spec-memory): boot integrity-check (detect-only) + retention durability + probe-liveness fix (026/007/012)
    
    - Boot FTS integrity-check, DETECT-ONLY: a .unclean-shutdown marker (written on DB open, deleted on
      clean close after the WAL TRUNCATE) gates an async-after-ready FTS5 'integrity-check' verb on the next
      boot; on failure -> health 'corrupt' + loud banner + runbook pointer (026/004/012). No auto rebuild/
      .recover/swap (auto-recover deferred). Marker path derived from getDbPath() (correct under MEMORY_DB_PATH)
    - Retention sweep durability: after deletes commit, best-effort FTS optimize + guarded incremental_vacuum
      (only if auto_vacuum=INCREMENTAL) + wal_checkpoint(TRUNCATE), all outside the delete tx
    - Probe-liveness: DEFAULT_PROBE_TIMEOUT_MS 2500 -> 5000 (env SPECKIT_PROBE_TIMEOUT_MS, clamped < 7000ms
      launcher grace); the reap/bridge decision REQUIRES a JSON-RPC reply (deepProbe), not a bare socket connect
    - Adversarial review caught a P1 (probe connect-ok disabled hung-daemon detection -> client bridged to a
      wedged daemon, never respawned) -> FIXED via deepProbe-required reap; 2 LOW (marker-dir divergence FIXED;
      marker-lingering-after-fatal-mismatch DOCUMENTED). tsc + 385 tests green
    - 3rd daemon-WAL-durability child (after 009/010); extends 008 checkpoint-on-close
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

