    fix(026): remediate last-50-commits deep-review findings — 017
    
    Remediate all actionable findings from the 016 deep review.
    
    Lifecycle/shutdown: fence the ingest worker before DB close (no
    reopen-after-close dirty WAL); unify the two divergent SIGTERM/SIGINT
    handler stacks into one ordered path with a deterministic exit code.
    IPC/socket: reject a symlink on fresh socket bind + lstat-guarded fchmod;
    fail-closed path canonicalization; re-entrant startIpcSocketServer guard;
    launcher lease fsync parity. Applied identically to both socket-server
    copies (drift test enforces byte-identity).
    Validator/memory: bound the session-id DFS (dir/depth/time caps);
    enrichment skip-guard also skips 'archived'; tighten the E089
    'access denied:' match; refresh a stale entity-density doc comment.
    Contract/config/docs: add embedder tools to TOOL_LAYER_MAP; drop dangling
    .gemini/agents refs from the .claude + .codex agent mirrors; add the HF
    single-owner socket notes to .codex/.devin configs; correct the 015 P0
    miscount (2 to 1).
    Tests: processLiveness drift guard; shutdown-fence + fresh-bind-symlink
    validation; auto-fix default-path, 3-node contradiction-cycle, and
    rollout-bucketing coverage; de-no-op'd 7 guarded assertions.
    Accepted no-action (see 017 decision-record): F-002, F-A3-01/02, F-CC-*.
    
    Verified: tsc 0 errors (mcp_server/shared/code-graph); 1055 affected +
    154 new/extended + 3 fork-parity tests pass; alignment-drift PASS; socket
    forks byte-identical. Source fixes take effect after build+deploy
    (deferred to operator).
    
